<div dir="ltr">A problem Siegmar reported on trunk over a year and a half ago is breaking a 32-bit build of the v1.8 branch with the Sun C++ compiler:<div><br></div><div>Siegmar&#39;s report appears in <a href="http://www.open-mpi.org/community/lists/users/2013/01/21269.php">http://www.open-mpi.org/community/lists/users/2013/01/21269.php</a></div>
<div>There are several warnings, but the error is (from my current build):</div><div><br></div><div><div>&quot;/shared/OMPI/openmpi-1.8-latest-solaris11-x86-ib-ss12u3/openmpi-1.8.2rc4r32480/ompi/mpi/cxx/file.cc&quot;, Error: The function opal_atomic_add_32(volatile int*, int) has not had a body defined.</div>
</div><div><br></div><div>Brian attached a possible fix to <a href="http://www.open-mpi.org/community/lists/users/2013/01/21272.php">http://www.open-mpi.org/community/lists/users/2013/01/21272.php</a></div><div>It applies cleanly to v1.8 but appears to make things worse, trading that one error for two:</div>
<div><br></div><div><div>&quot;/shared/OMPI/openmpi-1.8-latest-solaris11-x86-ib-ss12u3/openmpi-1.8.2rc4r32480/opal/include/opal/sys/atomic_impl.h&quot;, line 106: Error: opal_atomic_add_64(volatile long long*, long long) was previously declared &quot;extern&quot;, not &quot;inline&quot;.</div>
<div>&quot;/shared/OMPI/openmpi-1.8-latest-solaris11-x86-ib-ss12u3/openmpi-1.8.2rc4r32480/opal/include/opal/sys/atomic_impl.h&quot;, line 121: Error: opal_atomic_sub_64(volatile long long*, long long) was previously declared &quot;extern&quot;, not &quot;inline&quot;.</div>
</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>The good news is that the problem does not exist on the trunk.</div><div>So, hopefully somebody can track down the proper changes to CMR.</div><div><br></div><div>-Paul</div><div><br clear="all">
